name: Cats and Stars Tote by Lori Taesheler
description:
This is one-of-a kind bag that was specially produced for the Rachel Nasvik Project that benefited Stoked Mentoring. This bag was dyed red and then hand painted by Lori.

Rachel Nasvek a New York based bag designer, commissioned members of the creative elite to take ordinary canvas tote bags and make something unique and inspirational. Rachel hosted an Art show of all the bags at TG-170 in the Lower East Side of Manhattan.

name: TheCast Tote Bag
description:
THECAST is a New York based punk-rock clothing line and store. Rachel Nasvik asked THECAST's design team to create a bag for the Rachel Nasvik project to benefit Stoked. 

This tote is silk screened with one of THECASTs signature images. "THECAST" is pained in black on the back. 
Check out more of THECAST at THECAST.com

name: POW! Wonder Woman Tote
description: The Wonder Women picture on this tote bag was hand drawn by Mort Todd the editor of Cracked Magazine and Marvel Music. When Rachel Nasvik asked Mort to design a bag for her tote bag art show and project, Mort used the animation skills that had acquired from working on Superman, Spider Man and RatFink.

name: Shapes Tote
description:
This bag was designed by Evert Lee for the Rachel Nasvik project and art show to benefit Stoked. 

Evert is an architect and artist and this tote was hand painted by him. The back of the bag has additional shapes and colors

name: Zered Bassett Tote
description: Zered Bassett is a pro-skateboarder on the Zoo York Team. Transworld named Zered rookie of the year in 2005. This tote was hand painted by Zered for the Rachel Nasvik project and art show.
